Hlaudi Motsoeneng (Felix Dlanagamandla, Netwerk24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town - The Western Cape High Court has ruled that Hlaudi Motsoeneng cannot work at the SABC in any capacity unless a Public Protector's report is set aside, or a new disciplinary hearing clears him. ''Mr Motsoeneng should not be entitled to hold any position in the SABC unless and until the Pulbic Protector's report is set aside or the new disciplinary committee finds in his favour,'' Judge Owen Rogers said on Monday.The acting COO&nbsp;Bessie Tugwana's position was also set aside, but any decisions she took in that position before the judgment on Monday, remain valid.A new disciplinary committee has to be established, and clear timelines must be kept. Until those processes are finalised,&nbsp;Motsoeneng's appointment remains invalid. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.